iant of   Bussey  , of Norman origin. This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Bucey","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Bussey  ."]},{"name":"Busey","meanings":["English: variant of   Bussey  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"JOHN","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir JOHN De BUSSEY was born in 1350, in England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir WILLIAM De BUSSEY, was 25 and his mother, Isabelle Paynell, was 25. He married Maud de Nevill in 1382. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 30 July 1399, in his hometown, at the age of 49, and was buried in Hougham, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1350–30 July 1399":"1350–30. juuli 1399","1350–1399":"1350–1399","1361–1398":"1361–1398","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","1380–1459":"1380–1459","–1428":"–1428","1325–1380":"1325–1380","1325–1375":"1325–1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1459":"1459","24 October 1380":"24. oktoober 1380","1325":"1325","1399":"1399","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","30 July 1399":"30. juuli 1399","1428":"1428","Hougham, South Kesteven District, Lincolnshire, England":"Hougham, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dembleby, Sleaford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Dembleby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1350–30 July 1399":"1350–30. heinäkuuta 1399","1350–1399":"1350–1399","1361–1398":"1361–1398","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","1380–1459":"1380–1459","–1428":"–1428","1325–1380":"1325–1380","1325–1375":"1325–1375","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1459":"1459","24 October 1380":"24. lokakuuta 1380","1325":"1325","1399":"1399","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","30 July 1399":"30. heinäkuuta 1399","1428":"1428","Hougham, South Kesteven District, Lincoln